  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "edk2 security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for edk2 is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "EDK II is a modern, feature-rich, cross-platform firmware development environment for the UEFI and PI specifications.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA BIOS bug in firmware for a particular PC model leaves the Platform authorization value empty. This can be used to permanently brick the TPM in multiple ways, as well as to non-permanently DoS the system.(CVE-2021-38576)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for edk2 is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "edk2",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
